# **4. Instagram Integration Roadmap**

Given that the launch artist has 300K Instagram followers and an active Instagram shop, Instagram integration is a priority growth driver for B-Edge. The integration is planned in three stages of increasing depth.

| **Stage** | **Phase** | **Feature** | **Business Value** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Stage 1 | MVP | Share B-Edge profile link in Instagram bio | Immediate traffic from 300K followers at zero cost |
| Stage 1 | MVP | Instagram portfolio link on artist profile | Customers can see full Instagram before booking |
| Stage 2 | Phase 2 | Official Instagram Book Now button on profile | Customers book without leaving Instagram |
| Stage 2 | Phase 2 | Import portfolio photos from Instagram feed | Artists save time. Portfolio stays fresh automatically |
| Stage 2 | Phase 2 | Instagram story deep link to booking page | Story viewers land directly on booking screen |
| Stage 3 | Phase 3 | Instagram shop product sync | Artists sell products on B-Edge and Instagram from one catalogue |
| Stage 3 | Phase 3 | Instagram insights integration | Artists see which Instagram posts drive most bookings |
| Stage 3 | Phase 4 | Instagram DM to booking conversion | Convert Instagram DMs into B-Edge bookings automatically |

The Stage 1 integration requires zero technical work and zero API access. It is simply a link in the Instagram bio. This alone is enough to drive significant traffic on launch day given the 300K follower audience.

# **5. MVP Summary — What We Build in 7 Weeks**

The MVP contains everything needed to validate B-Edge with real Lebanese beauty artists and their customers. Nothing more. Nothing less.

## **5.1 Customer MVP**

- **Register and login with email and password**

- Search and filter artists by service, city, and price

- View artist profile, portfolio, services, and reviews

- Check availability and request a booking

- Receive email confirmation of booking

- View upcoming and past bookings

- Cancel a booking

- Leave a review after completed appointment

- Arabic and English interface

## **5.2 Artist MVP**

- **Register and set up full profile**

- Add services with prices and durations

- Upload portfolio photos

- Set working hours and block unavailable dates

- Receive and manage booking requests

- View client list with history and notes

- View earnings summary

- Share personal B-Edge booking link

## **5.3 What Is NOT In MVP**

| **Feature** | **Why Excluded** | **When Added** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Online payments | No payment gateway available in Lebanon | Phase 4 |
| Native mobile app | PWA covers this for MVP | Phase 3 |
| Instagram Book Now button | Requires Meta business review process | Phase 2 |
| In-app chat | WhatsApp still works for MVP | Phase 2 |
| Product catalogue | Out of scope for booking platform MVP | Phase 3 |
| SMS notifications | Email sufficient for MVP | Phase 2 |
| Push notifications | PWA install not required for MVP | Phase 2 |
| Analytics dashboard | Not needed until scale | Phase 3 |
| Multi country | Lebanon only for MVP | Phase 3 |
| Staff management | Solo artists only for MVP | Phase 3 |

# **6. Development Timeline**

| **Week** | **Focus** | **Deliverable** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Week 1 | Backend setup and database | Project structure, PostgreSQL schema, Auth API |
| Week 2 | Core API endpoints | Artist, booking, search, and review endpoints |
| Week 3 | Artist PWA | Profile setup, portfolio upload, services, calendar |
| Week 4 | Artist PWA | Bookings dashboard, client list, earnings view |
| Week 5 | Customer PWA | Home, search, artist profile, availability view |
| Week 6 | Customer PWA | Booking flow, confirmation screen, my bookings |
| Week 7 | Testing and deployment | Bug fixes, AWS deploy, give access to first artist |
| Month 2 to 3 | Feedback and fixes | Improve based on real usage from brother's girlfriend |
| Month 3 to 6 | Phase 2 features | Instagram integration, SMS, chat, rebook |
| Month 6 to 12 | Phase 3 features | MENA expansion, products, analytics |
| Year 2 | Phase 4 features | Payments, AI, white label, API |

